video:video.video:description: Latvia's Ambassador to Ukraine said Russia’s attack on a thermal power plant in Kyiv was "a war crime" and "genocidal". (AP video: Srdjan Nedeljkovic & Dmytro Zhyhinas)

video:video.video:title: Team USA’s first Olympic stop: a head-to-toe Ralph Lauren fitting near Milan - AP Explains
video:video.video:description: Athletes from the USA team participating in the Milan-Cortina Winter Olympics made a first stop on Wednesday to tailor their ceremony outfits, designed by Ralph Lauren.

video:video.video:title: Snoop Dogg takes part in Winter Olympic torch relay
video:video.video:description: Snoop Dogg drew a crowd on Wednesday as the music superstar took part in the Milan Cortina Winter Olympics torch relay.

video:video.video:title: Turning Point USA presents alternative show to Bad Bunny Super Bowl performance
video:video.video:description: The Patriots and Seahawks won’t be the only competition during the Super Bowl this Sunday. Turning Point USA says it plans to put on an alternative event to Bad Bunny’s halftime performance.

video:video.video:title: Mandelson "betrayed our country" with links to Epstein, U.K. PM says
video:video.video:description: British police opened a criminal investigation into former Ambassador to the U.S. Peter Mandelson over alleged misconduct in public office related to his relationship with the late convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.

video:video.video:title: The former Prince Andrew moves to King Charles III’s private estate after Epstein document uproar
video:video.video:description: The former Prince Andrew has moved out of his longtime home on crown-owned land near Windsor Castle earlier than expected, after the latest release of documents from the U.S. investigation of Jeffrey Epstein revived questions about his friendship with the convicted sex offender.

video:video.video:title: Melinda French Gates speaks about Bill Gates in the Epstein files
video:video.video:description: Philanthropist Melinda French Gates says her ex-husband Bill Gates needs to ‘answer to those things,’ referring to allegations about Gates made by the late convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein in recently released files.

video:video.video:title: Trump taking steps toward installing a Columbus statue near the White House
video:video.video:description: President Donald Trump is taking steps toward installing near the White House a replica of a statue of famed explorer Christopher Columbus that had been tossed into Baltimore’s harbor during his first term amid protests against institutional racism.

video:video.video:title: Vigil held at Tucson church for kidnapped mother of NBC 'Today' show host Savannah Guthrie
video:video.video:description: A vigil was held late Wednesday for the missing mother of NBC “Today” show host Savannah Guthrie at St. Philip's in the Hills Episcopal Church in Tucson, Arizona.

video:video.video:title: Bangladesh's Hindu minority in fear as attacks rise and national election nears
video:video.video:description: Dipu Chandra Das, a 27-year-old Hindu garment worker, was accused in December by several Muslim colleagues of making derogatory remarks about the Prophet Muhammad.

video:video.video:title: Syria signs landmark offshore oil field deal with Chevron and Qatari investor
video:video.video:description: Syria’s state-owned petroleum company signed a memorandum of understanding with U.S. and Qatari companies on Wednesday for the development of the country’s first offshore oil and gas field.

video:video.video:title: Savannah Guthrie posts message to her mother's kidnapper asking to provide proof she is alive
video:video.video:description: NBC “Today” show host Savannah Guthrie said her family is ready to talk to people holding their mother, but they want to see proof that she is alive.

video:video.video:title: Residents of compound sheltering Syrians displaced in Lebanon deny being Assad loyalists
video:video.video:description: The residents of a walled compound in Lebanon, housing hundreds of Syrians and Lebanese who fled their homes after the fall of Syria’s Bashar Assad 14 months ago, have denied being Assad loyalists.
